---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "tools for electronics — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>tools for electronics</h1>
    <p>small, friendly tools that make building neat and calm.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      starter picks: flush cutters, wire strippers, tweezers, <strong>60 W temp-controlled iron</strong>, 63/37 solder, flux pen, wick, basic multimeter, breadboard + jumpers.
    </div>

    <h2>essentials</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>flush cutters</strong> – trim leads cleanly.</li>
      <li><strong>wire strippers</strong> – 22 AWG solid for breadboards; 24–28 AWG stranded for cables.</li>
      <li><strong>tweezers</strong> – ESD-safe makes SMD calm.</li>
      <li><strong>soldering iron</strong> – ~330–360 °C leaded, 360–380 °C lead-free; sponge or brass wool.</li>
      <li><strong>solder</strong> – 0.6–0.8 mm; 63/37 is easy. keep a <strong>flux pen</strong> + wick handy.</li>
      <li><strong>multimeter (DMM)</strong> – DC volts, resistance, continuity beep are the daily drivers.</li>
      <li><strong>breadboard &amp; jumpers</strong> – prototype without solder.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>nice to have</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>bench supply</strong> with current limit.</li>
      <li><strong>hot air</strong> or rework station; heat-shrink &amp; hot glue for cables.</li>
      <li><strong>logic analyzer</strong> for I²C/SPI mysteries; an <strong>oscilloscope</strong> for waves.</li>
      <li><strong>ESD strap</strong>, Kapton tape, helping-hands or PCB vise.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>quick DMM sketch</h2>
    <div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="measure DC voltage with a multimeter across a part">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 560 180" width="100%" height="auto">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="560" height="180" rx="16" fill="var(--card)"/>
        <!-- circuit under test -->
        <text x="36" y="44" class="mono">+5V</text>
        <line x1="70" y1="40" x2="220" y2="40" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <rect x="220" y="30" width="36" height="20" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="214" y="24" class="mono mini">R</text>
        <line x1="256" y1="40" x2="340" y2="40" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <line x1="340" y1="40" x2="340" y2="140" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <line x1="60"  y1="140" x2="340" y2="140" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="32" y="144" class="mono">0V</text>

        <!-- DMM box -->
        <rect x="380" y="30" width="150" height="100" rx="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="455" y="62" text-anchor="middle" class="mono">DMM</text>
        <text x="455" y="82" text-anchor="middle" class="mono mini">DC V</text>
        <!-- probes -->
        <circle cx="430" cy="120" r="4" fill="currentColor"/>
        <circle cx="480" cy="120" r="4" fill="currentColor"/>
        <text x="420" y="138" class="mono mini">COM</text>
        <text x="472" y="138" class="mono mini">VΩ</text>
        <!-- leads to circuit -->
        <line x1="430" y1="120" x2="320" y2="140" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <line x1="480" y1="120" x2="320" y2="40"  stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="326" y="28" class="mono mini">measure across</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h2>tiny safety</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>ventilation for solder fumes; wash hands after leaded solder.</li>
      <li>eye protection when cutting leads.</li>
      <li>for current measurements, move the red lead to the A/mA jack and wire the meter <em>in series</em> — double-check range &amp; fuse.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
